        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Setting get or post values and not resetting them afterwards will leak the values to subsequent tests. This appears to be because the HttpTestCase request methods set values in $_POST and $_GET, and later on, the new instances of the request load the old values from the superglobals.\n\nI think it would make more sense if the $_POST\/$_GET values would not persist between tests. This may also affect $_COOKIE, but I haven't tested that."
        },
