        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24288",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This bug is a real show-stopper if you're running multiple controller test within one run and you must rely on clean request contexts.\nFor example I'm using a {{preDispatch()}} plugin that loads model entities and persits them inside the request object with {{$request->setParam('xy', ...)}}. There are cases when there is no model entity to be set (entity not found), so I check for  {{if (!$this->_getParam('xy'))}}  in my controller to forward to a 404-page. No problem so far.\nI also run tests on my authentication controller where I set the request data inside my test method with {{$this->getRequest()->setPost(array( [...], 'xy' => 'someValue', [...]));}}. 'someValue' is no persisted throughout the complete test run inside the {{$_POST}} global array, so the controller test in which the controller uses {{if (!$this->_getParam('xy'))}} does not work anymore if this test is executed after the authentication tests because the 'xy' param does not contain a model instance but rather the string 'someValue' from a previous test run on an authentication controller test.\n\nEither  {{Zend_Controller_Request_HttpTestCase}} should use an internal array to store  {{$_GET}} and {{$_POST}} data, which could easily be resetted by creating a new request instance, or {{Zend_Test_PHPUnit_ControllerTestCase}} must issue a \n{code}\n$_GET=array();\n$_POST=array();\n{code}\nin its {{setUp()}} method.\n\nI didn't do any tests with cookies so I cannot comment on if there is a problem with $_COOKIE too. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-09-05T10:32:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-09-05T10:32:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24443",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fixed in trunk and 1.6 release branch; $_GET, $_POST, $_COOKIE, and $_SESSION are all reset during reset() now.\n\nFix will ship with 1.6.1.",
